<br>Ufdah 38 Mercenary  Home Lancelot</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukainyar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kainyar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/02 9:08:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1866.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letter to Sanya (Hibernia, Assassins)</span><hr size=1> Ok,<br>
<br>
Remember you asked for comments!<br>
<br>
1) I think you should be banned from using words such as &quot;concise&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Hehe of course you pointed this out as well but still had to poke a lil fun.  Really though, you may want to consider presenting these issues in part rather than in totality.  I don't know how Sanya is regarding email but if I were going to compare it to say a recruiter (comparison because I know some who get a great volume of email traffic) who is overwhelmed with resumes and emails, they will look at the load of mail to go through and when they come to long letters that take a significant amount of time to read they get filed.  Maybe instead break up your analysis into volumes, such as Vol1: Critical Strikes.. Vol2: Assassins vs Archers... you get the point.  Besides being able to be concise because you have limited your subject matter you may also gain name recognition with Sanya.  <br>
<br>
2) Might want to consider not referring to the person you are sending the email to in the 3rd person.<br>
&quot;Sanya also posted on the...&quot;<br>
<br>
3)  Regarding Hibernia being the redheaded step child, I was under the impression that part of this is also because the realm in general does not seem as finished as the other realms in design and class balance testing etc... What were your impressions to this point?<br>
<br>
4)  I personally think your Archers vs Assassins analysis didn't go far enough.  There was alot of data there but the meat of the matter is in combat Archers generate so much more damage that they do our job in a more deadly and efficient manner while benefitting from greater armor, and safety of the ranged attack.  Furthermore in Hibernia Nightshades are supposed to be strong spell casters but Rangers have better magical abilities as well!  Maybe Ranger spells are not offensive but the Nightshade's offensive spell is fairly weak anyway and I would trade it in a heartbeat for an escape spell or a self buff or two.<br>
<br>
4.a)  I would like to know (perhaps you know the answer to this) if their stealth is gimped at all by wearing reinforced armor?  What is the benefit for us for wearing leather?  Is safe fall and climb our offsetting abilities?<br>
<br>
4.b)  As an archer if I am out of range I simply do not loose my arrow, but as an assassin if I am out of range to perform an attack I fail in my attack and drop stealth.  I think it is easier to know I am our of arms reach then to know my target is 5 feet out of my arrows flight.  I think if positional requirements are not eliminated from critical strikes then two other ideas should be considered.  <br>
<br>
 - First we should not enter combat if we are not in position to perform the attack.  Give us a message but dont drop stealth.  Heck we all know if we sit there long enough we are going to be uncovered anyway so there is still a risk.<br>
<br>
 - Secondly, we should also get the ability to stack attacks like the archers do.  As an archer I can line up my crit, and automatically release and begin my next attack, but if I hit my next style key too soon it tells me I am already doing something else. <br>
<br>
<br>
Well thats enough red ink from me (I mean who am I anyway?) but I would be interested to hear if you received a response.<br>
<br>
